                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_108038">Thrupp</placeName>.

   <persName>
                           <forename>James</forename>, prior of <orgName role="prior" key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </orgName>
                        </persName>, grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename> 
                           <surname>Caterich</surname>
                        </persName> and his heirs of <placeName key="place_108038">Trop</placeName> for his homage and service, the virgate in <placeName key="place_108038">T<supplied>hrupp</supplied>
                        </placeName> which Henry his father held, for a mark down and half a mark of silver a year.
<pb n="113"/>
He shall mow, reap and plough three times in the year. 
Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </surname>
                        </persName>,
   <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> de <surname>Trop</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   Roger G——, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Warner</forename> of <surname>Trop</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> the knight</persName>,
   <persName>
                           <forename>Simon</forename> 
                           <surname>Campioun</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   Nigel, <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> the <surname>porter</surname>
                        </persName>. 
   <origDate notBefore="1210" notAfter="1225">
                           <supplied>1210–25.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
